Description of aspects of trollbot:

Events:
  In order to maintain a somewhat generic format for different protocols, I need a way to make events, and match event handlers to the events if
they occur. each event will consist of matchtext, the raw data, and a matching function. For instance:

raw data = PING irc.mudportal.com

int matchfunc(void *, void *)

matchtext "PING"


core - deals with sockets, registers events, registers event handlers, registers modules, supplies API for modules. registers config file extensions,
maintains config namespaces, provides utility functions.


Modules:

irc       - Deals with everything IRC related, sets up the events, adds sockets to socket loop.
scripting - registers event handlers for events
dcc       - Supplies a partyline and management console
crypto    - Provides a cryptographic library for hashing of passwords and other uses

if WITH_TCL

trollbot_SOURCES += tcl_embed.c tcl_lib.c tcl_embed.h tcl_lib.h
trollbot_CFLAGS  += ${TCL_CPPFLAGS}
trollbot_LDADD   += ${TCL_LIBS}

endif

if WITH_PHP

trollbot_SOURCES += apachecompat.c php_embed.c php_lib.c apachecompat.h php_embed.h php_lib.h
trollbot_CFLAGS  += ${PHP_CFLAGS}
trollbot_LDADD   += ${PHP_LDADD}

endif

if WITH_PERL

trollbot_SOURCES += perl_embed.c perl_lib.c perl_embed.h perl_lib.h
trollbot_CFLAGS  += ${PERL_CFLAGS}
trollbot_LDADD   += ${PERL_LDADD}

endif

if WITH_PYTHON

trollbot_SOURCES += python_embed.c python_lib.c python_embed.h python_lib.h
trollbot_CFLAGS  += ${PYTHON_CFLAGS}
trollbot_LDADD   += ${PYTHON_LDADD}

endif

